\subsection*{7.0 TYPE II RESPIRATORY FAILURE}

Results from alveolar hypoventilation and is commonly from chronic bronchitis and emphysema. There is decreased $\mathrm{PaO}_{2}$ and increased $\mathrm{PaCO}_{2}$ ( $>6.7 \mathrm{kPa} / 50 \mathrm{mmHg}$ )

\section*{Causes}
