$\checkmark$ Ingestion from self-swallowing of infected sputum of an open case of pulmonary tuberculosis or ingestion of bovine tubercle bacilli from milk of diseased cows resulting in tonsilar or intestinal tuberculosis.
$\checkmark$ Ingestion is nowadays rare due to pasteurization of milk
