\subsection*{1.0 INTRODUCTION}

Most emboli arise from deep leg veins (calf, popliteal, femoral and iliac veins) and passes in the venous circulation into the right heart and to the pulmonary arteries. Pulmonary embolism is a common preventable condition that can cause arterial occlusion resulting in infarction.

